videos.description: Beaver Stadium erupts after hearing that Ohio State defeated Michigan in double overtime, clearing the way for Penn State to win the Big Ten East with a victory over Michigan State.
videos.headline: Penn State fans erupt at news of Michigan's loss

videos.headline: Michigan State's starting QB and RB leave game with injury

videos.description: Michigan State gets stopped in the red zone again, forcing Michael Geiger into hitting his third field goal of the game, boosting the Spartans' lead to 9-3.
videos.headline: Greiger drills third FG for Michigan State

videos.description: Saquon Barkley takes to the sky and gets over the pile to score from a yard out to give Penn State the 10-9 lead.
videos.headline: Barkley flies over the pile for Penn State TD

videos.description: Michael Geiger goes 4-for-4 on field goals, putting Michigan State up 12-10 as the teams head into the locker room.
videos.headline: Michigan State takes lead into halftime with another FG

videos.description: Penn State head coach James Franklin discusses team's improvements for 2nd half
videos.headline: Penn State head coach James Franklin discusses team's improvements for 2nd half

videos.description: Chris Godwin runs the double move to perfection, leaving him wide open for Trace McSorley to find with a 34-yard touchdown pass giving Penn State back the lead.
videos.headline: Godwin's double move good for 34-yard Penn State TD

videos.description: Trace McSorley airs it out, going deep to Mike Gesicki who makes the spectacular catch between a pair of defenders and scores to increase Penn State's lead to 24-12.
videos.headline: Gesicki's spectacular catch scores another Penn State TD

videos.headline: Saquon Barkley leaves game with apparent ankle injury

videos.description: Trace McSorley has it going on, throwing for his third long touchdown pass of the third quarter, this one to Chris Godwin for 59 yards to boost the Penn State lead to 31-12.
videos.headline: Penn State airs it out for another long TD

videos.description: Andre Robinson takes the handoff and goes up the middle for a 14-yard touchdown that has Penn State booking their tickets to Indianapolis for the Big Ten title game.
videos.headline: Robinson's TD has Penn State smelling Big Ten East title
